Method Detail

findByPropertyName

public static ConfigToken<?> findByPropertyName(String propertyName)

applyConfiguration

public static Map<ConfigToken<?>,Object> applyConfiguration(Map<ConfigToken<?>,Object> stagingConf,
                                                            HtmlTable table)

Overloads the configurations stored in the TableConfiguration instance with the one passed as parameter.

Parameters:
stagingConf - The staging configurations filled either with the JSP taglib or with the Thymeleaf dialect.
table - The table which holds the TableConfiguration to overload.

processConfiguration

public static Map<ConfigToken<?>,Object> processConfiguration(HtmlTable table)

At this point, the configuration stored inside the TableConfiguration contains only Strings. All these strings will be processed in this method, depending on the ConfigToken they are bound to.

Once processed, all strings will be replaced by the typed value.

Only configuration token with not blank values will be merged into the TableConfiguration instance.

Parameters:
table - The table which holds the configuration to process.
